{
  "article_id": "TheNewYorkPress1901",
  "paragraphs": [
    [
      {
        "text": "An air of mystery pervades each of ",
        "tropes": [
          5
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the little islands",
        "tropes": [
          5
        ],
        "entity_key": "i_chi",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": " in the scant archipelago off the coast of ",
        "tropes": [
          5
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "California.",
        "tropes": [
          5
        ],
        "entity_key": "st_cal",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "San Clemente Island",
        "tropes": [
          5
        ],
        "entity_key": "i_scl",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": " is strewn with enormous prehistoric mortars and pestles, and here and there are numerous evidences that ",
        "tropes": [
          5
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "a giant race",
        "tropes": [
          5
        ],
        "entity_key": "natam_GabrilenoTongva",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": " lived there before the Portuguese navigator, ",
        "tropes": [
          5
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "Cabrillo",
        "tropes": [
          5
        ],
        "entity_key": "jca",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ", sailed for conquest up the coast of ",
        "tropes": [
          5
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "Alta, California",
        "tropes": [
          5
        ],
        "entity_key": "re_local",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", in 1542. ",
        "tropes": [
          5
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "Santa Catalina",
        "tropes": [
          5
        ],
        "entity_key": "i_scatalina",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": " is indented by many strange caves, weird grottoes, where one may see remains of ",
        "tropes": [
          5
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "a race of fishers and artisans",
        "tropes": [
          5
        ],
        "entity_key": "natam_GabrilenoTongva",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": " with shells. ",
        "tropes": [
          5
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "San Miguel Island",
        "tropes": [
          5
        ],
        "entity_key": "i_sm",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": " has been the scene of titanic erosions by ice, water and sand. The grotesque pillars that lift themselves above the island level, the winding caves that twist from the shores into the heart of ",
        "tropes": [
          5
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the island",
        "tropes": [
          5
        ],
        "entity_key": "i_sm",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": " and the roaring gulches and canyons all comprise a spot rich in possibilities for both scientist and dreamer. ",
        "tropes": [
          5
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "Santa Cruz Island",
        "tropes": [
          5
        ],
        "entity_key": "i_scruz",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": " is used as a pasturage for thousands of sheep, and it. [sic] too, is full of absorbing interest regarding extinct races of ",
        "tropes": [
          5
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "aborigines",
        "tropes": [
          5
        ],
        "entity_key": "natam_chumash",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": ". The Smithsonian Institution scientists have gathered tons of stone, shell and bone utensils and personal ornaments from ",
        "tropes": [
          5
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "Santa Cruz",
        "tropes": [
          5
        ],
        "entity_key": "i_scruz",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ". ",
        "tropes": [
          5
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": " But ",
        "tropes": [
          6,
          5
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "San Nicolas Island",
        "tropes": [
          6,
          5
        ],
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "has by far the most abundant evidences of ",
        "tropes": [
          6,
          5
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "a tribe",
        "tropes": [
          6,
          5
        ],
        "entity_key": "natam_NicolenoTongva",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": "of unusually tall and strong people who must have vanished almost in a night. Of all ",
        "tropes": [
          6,
          5
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the California archipelago",
        "tropes": [
          6,
          5
        ],
        "entity_key": "i_chi",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "this is the most mysterious.",
        "tropes": [
          6,
          5
        ]
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "Notwithstanding "
      },
      {
        "text": "the islands",
        "entity_key": "i_chi",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "—known on the "
      },
      {
        "text": "Pacific coast",
        "entity_key": "re_paccoast",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": " as "
      },
      {
        "text": "the Channel Islands",
        "entity_key": "i_chi",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "—are but thirty to fifty miles out in the blues of the ocean, they seldom are visited. Every few years an exploring expedition goes to them for a season of scientific study, but, with the exception of "
      },
      {
        "text": "Santa Catalina",
        "entity_key": "i_scatalina",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "—a famous summer resort for "
      },
      {
        "text": "California",
        "entity_key": "st_cal",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": " pleasure-seekers and anglers—a half-dozen visitors do not land at any of "
      },
      {
        "text": "the islands",
        "entity_key": "i_chi",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": " once a year. To-day "
      },
      {
        "text": "the islands",
        "entity_key": "i_chi",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": " remain as lonely and desolate as they did long before the first white face sailed up the coast—360 years ago. "
      },
      {
        "text": "The races",
        "tropes": [
          5,
          6
        ],
        "entity_keys": [
          "natam_NicolenoTongva",
          "natam_GabrilenoTongva",
          "natam_chumash"
        ],
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": " which occupied ",
        "tropes": [
          5,
          6
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "these islands",
        "tropes": [
          5,
          6
        ],
        "entity_key": "i_chi",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": " are as much of a mystery as ever, and so far science is baffled in inquiring what sort of folk ",
        "tropes": [
          5,
          6
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "these aboriginal settlers",
        "tropes": [
          5,
          6
        ],
        "entity_keys": [
          "natam_NicolenoTongva",
          "natam_GabrilenoTongva",
          "natam_chumash"
        ],
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": " were, how they lived, what they believed, and especially how they so suddenly and completely disappeared from the face of the earth. ",
        "tropes": [
          5,
          6
        ]
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "The University of California, at Berkeley",
        "entity_key": "in_ucb",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": ", is about to begin the most thorough exploration ever made of "
      },
      {
        "text": "San Nicolas Island",
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", which lies sixty miles off the coast of "
      },
      {
        "text": "Ventura",
        "entity_key": "co_ventura",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "and "
      },
      {
        "text": "Santa Barbara counties.",
        "entity_key": "co_sb",
        "entity_type": "place"
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "As far back as the memory of any person in "
      },
      {
        "text": "southern California",
        "entity_key": "re_socal",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": " runs, hundreds of white skeletons have dotted the valleys and hillsides of "
      },
      {
        "text": "San Nicolas",
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ". "
      },
      {
        "text": "Strange utensils of serpentine, sandstone and steatite are found there among the human bones, and ",
        "tropes": [
          5
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the island",
        "tropes": [
          5
        ],
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": " and ",
        "tropes": [
          5
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "its inhabitants",
        "tropes": [
          5
        ],
        "entity_key": "lw",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": " have a history so curious that it is difficult of comprehension.",
        "tropes": [
          5
        ]
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "In 1835 ",
        "tropes": [
          6
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the Franciscan padres in the Santa Barbara mission",
        "tropes": [
          6
        ],
        "entity_keys": [
          "aji",
          "ndur",
          "misfats"
        ],
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ", learning that there were but ",
        "tropes": [
          6
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "sixteen of the strange and almost extinct Indian race",
        "tropes": [
          6
        ],
        "entity_key": "bhagroup",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": " then living there, determined to rescue them from ",
        "tropes": [
          6
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the island",
        "tropes": [
          6
        ],
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ". They went over in "
      },
      {
        "text": "a sloop",
        "entity_key": "sh_peoresnada",
        "entity_type": "ship"
      },
      {
        "text": " and succeeded, as they thought, in getting all on board. At the last moment "
      },
      {
        "text": "an Indian woman",
        "entity_key": "lw",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": " returned for "
      },
      {
        "text": "her child",
        "entity_key": "lwchild",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ", and one of the frequent storms of "
      },
      {
        "text": "the Channel Isla[nds]",
        "entity_key": "i_chi",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": " springing up, "
      },
      {
        "text": "the sloop",
        "entity_key": "sh_peoresnada",
        "entity_type": "ship"
      },
      {
        "text": " was driven aw[ay] without her. "
      },
      {
        "text": "The sloop",
        "tropes": [
          6
        ],
        "entity_key": "sh_peoresnada",
        "entity_type": "ship"
      },
      {
        "text": " went on the rocks of ",
        "tropes": [
          6
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "Point Conception",
        "tropes": [
          6
        ],
        "entity_key": "re_pc",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": " and ",
        "tropes": [
          6
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "all on board",
        "tropes": [
          6
        ],
        "entity_key": "bhagroup",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": " were lost.",
        "tropes": [
          6
        ]
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "Sixteen years later "
      },
      {
        "text": "Captain George Nidever",
        "entity_key": "gni",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": " and "
      },
      {
        "text": "two men",
        "entity_keys": [
          "tje",
          "nativeamericans"
        ],
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": " went from "
      },
      {
        "text": "the coast",
        "entity_key": "re_calcoast",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": " on "
      },
      {
        "text": "a sloop",
        "entity_key": "sh_nidever",
        "entity_type": "ship"
      },
      {
        "text": " to hunt sea otter off "
      },
      {
        "text": "San Nicolas",
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ". "
      },
      {
        "text": "On landing, they were, like Crusoe, astonished to find human footprints in the sand. They saw no one, however, and a storm compelled them to put to sea.",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ]
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "It was two years thereafter that ",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the adventurous captain",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ],
        "entity_key": "gni",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ", revolving in his mind the sight of the footprints in ",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the uncanny island",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ],
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", determined to go and discover and bring over ",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the lonely woman",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ],
        "entity_key": "lw",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": " of whom he had vaguely heard. ",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "Men",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ],
        "entity_keys": [
          "cdi",
          "col",
          "msh",
          "poli",
          "nsk",
          "hva"
        ],
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": " accompanied him, and at length they saw on the surf-beaten shore ",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "a woman",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ],
        "entity_key": "lw",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": " with long tawny hair, dressed in a queer garb of colored bird skins, and scraping with a bone knife the blubber from a seal.",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ]
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "They surrounded and approached her stealthily, and although suddenly confronted, she did not appear in the least afraid, but smiled, and then, falling on her knees, prayed to the sun. ",
        "tropes": [
          1
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "The wild woman",
        "tropes": [
          1
        ],
        "entity_key": "lw",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": " offered no objection when by signs she was made to understand that she was to go with them in ",
        "tropes": [
          1
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the boat",
        "tropes": [
          1
        ],
        "entity_key": "sh_nidever",
        "entity_type": "ship"
      },
      {
        "text": ".",
        "tropes": [
          1
        ]
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "The[y] reached "
      },
      {
        "text": "Santa Barbara",
        "entity_key": "ci_sb",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": " across the rough sea, and the first thing "
      },
      {
        "text": "the Indian woman",
        "entity_key": "lw",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": " saw was "
      },
      {
        "text": "Dr. S. L. Shaw",
        "entity_key": "ssh",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ", now 80 years old, and yet living there, riding a horse. She had never seen or heard of any object like it, and thought "
      },
      {
        "text": "the man",
        "entity_key": "ssh",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": " and horse were one, and she knelt on the shore and offered her devotions to it. "
      },
      {
        "text": "Two weeks afterward ",
        "tropes": [
          6
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the last inhabitant",
        "tropes": [
          6
        ],
        "entity_key": "lw",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": " of ",
        "tropes": [
          6
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "rock-ribbed, tempest-tossed San Nicolas",
        "tropes": [
          6
        ],
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": " died from eating food to which she was unaccustomed, furnished by her rescuers, and the curtain fell on ",
        "tropes": [
          6
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "her race",
        "tropes": [
          6
        ],
        "entity_key": "natam_NicolenoTongva",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": "forever. ",
        "tropes": [
          6
        ]
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "In speaking of that death at a meeting of the "
      },
      {
        "text": "Southern California Medical Society",
        "entity_key": "socalmedicalsociety",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": " the other day "
      },
      {
        "text": "Dr. Walter Lindley",
        "entity_key": "wli",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": " said that if "
      },
      {
        "text": "the woman",
        "entity_key": "lw",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": " could have been spared a few years of life a story of "
      },
      {
        "text": "one of the strangest races",
        "entity_key": "natam_NicolenoTongva",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": " that ever lived in "
      },
      {
        "text": "the Southwest",
        "entity_key": "re_sw",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "and that had no contamination with the whites might have been learned. "
      },
      {
        "text": "The woman",
        "entity_key": "lw",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ", known as the \"Lone Woman of San Nicolas,\" has been the subject of a score of romances and poems and food for a lot of philosophy on the "
      },
      {
        "text": "Pacific coast",
        "entity_key": "re_paccoast",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": " for years."
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "San Nicolas",
        "tropes": [
          5
        ],
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": " is ten miles long and four miles wide at the widest point. Its topography shows a nearly level plateau, with an elevation of 800 to 1,000 feet. Two-thirds of the surface is covered with drifting sand, and the remainder grows a species of nutritious grass and moss on which a thousand sheep find pasture. Several springs have been discovered, but their water is slightly brackish. Of late years ",
        "tropes": [
          5
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the island",
        "tropes": [
          5
        ],
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": " is rarely visited, except by sheepshearers and shell gatherers, who make annual trips in schooners, fishing smacks and Chinese junks.",
        "tropes": [
          5
        ]
      }
    ]
  ]
}